arguments.body:
🟡 **Medium — `enableBeta()` mutates `readonly` properties via unsafe double casts.**

```ts
(this as { serviceVersion: string }).serviceVersion = previewServiceVersion;
(this as { apiVersion: string }).apiVersion = previewServiceVersion;
this.client["_client"].apiVersion = previewServiceVersion;
```

`serviceVersion` and `apiVersion` are declared `readonly` on the class. The cast `this as { serviceVersion: string }` strips the readonly modifier to allow mutation — this is the TypeScript equivalent of a `const_cast` in C++. It silently violates the contract the type system is enforcing.

More importantly, this is a **permanent side-effect on the original instance**, not just on the returned view. Any code that holds a reference to the original `SearchIndexClient` will now silently be making requests to the preview endpoint, even if it never called `enableBeta()`.

**Fix:** Have `enableBeta()` construct a *new* client (or a thin proxy/wrapper) that uses the preview API version, rather than mutating the existing instance. This keeps the stable client stable and makes the scope of the mutation explicit.
